Quote: EVERLASTING PEA (<i>Lathyrus latifolius</i>) is like a sweet pea, with a purple flower. It is a serious pest around Blenheim. [1967: is a rampant growing, tendril bearing scrambler, with red, pink or white flowers. It is a troublesome weed in hedgerous and waste places in South Island districts.]
